                                                                                        Introduction to SIEM — Task-Wise Answers

Task 1 — What does SIEM stand for?
• Security Information and Event Management system

Task 2 — Network Visibility through SIEM
2.1 Is registry-related activity host-centric or network-centric? → Host-centric
2.2 Is VPN-related activity host-centric or network-centric? → Network-centric

Task 3 — Log Sources and Log Ingestion
• In which location within a Linux environment are HTTP logs stored? → /var/log/httpd

Task 5 — Analysing Logs and Alerts
5.1 Which Event ID is generated when event logs are removed? → 104
5.2 What type of alert may require tuning? → False Alarm

Task 6 — Lab Work
6.1 Which process caused the alert? → cudominer.exe
6.2 Which user was responsible for the event that caused the alert? → chris.fort
6.3 Which host was involved? → HR_02
6.4 Which term in the rule matched and caused the alert? → miner
6.5 What is the best option that represents the event? → True-Positive
6.6 What is the FLAG? → THM{000_SIEM_INTRO}
